#Text=US presidential candidate Duncan Hunter speaks to Wikinews
#Text=Wednesday , January 2 , 2008

#Text=Duncan Hunter is an American politician who has been a Republican member of the House of Representatives since 1981 from California 's 52nd congressional district in northern and eastern San Diego .
#Text=It was previously numbered the 42nd District from 1981 to 1983 and then the 45th District from 1983 to 1993 .
#Text=Hunter was the chairman of the House Armed Services Committee during the 109th Congress .
#Text=Hunter is currently seeking the Republican Party nomination for President of the United States .
#Text=Below is David Shankbone 's interview with the Congressman .
#Text=Running for President
#Text=How do you handle juggling running the Presidential campaign , acting as a Congressman , and as a husband ?
#Text=It all works out well .
#Text=I just talked to my wife , who is campaigning in Wyoming right now .
#Text=She ’s in Casper ; I just saw her a couple of nights ago and I came back here [ to Washington D.C. ] for the votes [ on the Defense Bill ] .
#Text=Our son just came back from Afghanistan on Thanksgiving .
#Text=He ’s a U.S. Marine and finished his third tour there in Afghanistan and Iraq .
#Text=We ’re all doing well .
#Text=We ’re all blessed and having a great campaign season .
#Text=Do you ever at night say to yourself , “ I ca n’t believe I am finding the energy for another day of this . ”
#Text=No , actually , listen , most of this stuff is done in air conditioning . [ Laughs ]
#Text=[ Laughs ]
#Text=That ca n’t help the sleep deprivation , though .
#Text=Listen , I was looking out the window of the Capitol and I saw two guys laying pipeline across Independence Avenue and I thought all I have to do is straighten my tie and make another speech .
#Text=Good point .
#Text=It ’s a lot of fun , it ’s a privilege and we ’re having a great time .
#Text=It ’s a wonderful family endeavor .
#Text=I think we ’re getting our message out , too : strong national defense , enforce our borders ; we ’ve got the other guys talking about border enforcement and building my border fence .
#Text=Also , we ’re talking about bringing back high-paying manufacturing jobs that we pushed off to China with bad trade deals .
#Text=Also the need to keep this country strong militarily .
#Text=I think it ’s a strong message , and I think the message is catching hold well .
#Text=Immigration and the U.S.-Mexico border fence

#Text=Presumably the primary reason one typically gives to run for President is because they think they can win and do some good things for the country , but would you say the second reason after that is for a chance to frame the debate on the issues ?
#Text=Certainly .
#Text=I think you do that every day , so you ’re accomplishing something every day of the campaign , which is getting your message out .

#Text=For example , I built the border fence in San Diego and I wrote the law that the President signed last October 26 a year ago to extend the border fence — my San Diego fence — 854 miles across Arizona , New Mexico and Texas .
#Text=Across the smuggling corridors in those states .
#Text=So every day we work that issue and energize the American people to build the fence , which is now the law .
#Text=Every time we get that agenda to complete the border fence picked up by the other candidates , we are accomplishing something .
#Text=We ’re moving the ball down the field .
